María Esther Aguilar Cansimbe was a Mexican human rights defender and activist who worked to expose violence and abuses in her community. Activists like her often face threats, intimidation, and violence from powerful groups trying to silence their voices. In such dangerous environments, secure communication is vital to protect sensitive information and ensure personal safety.

Using offline, end-to-end encrypted messaging tools helps reduce the risk of surveillance and interception, allowing activists to share information discreetly. Important concepts to explore include human rights defense, digital security, encrypted messaging, offline communication, and protecting activists.